    <section class="resume-faq" aria-label="Resume frequently asked questions">
      <div class="faq-bubbles">
      <button
        type="button"
        class="faq-bubble"
        data-faq-question="Why am I looking for a new role?"
        data-faq-answer="I value my current organization and team, and I am grateful for the opportunities I have had there. Over time, I integrated automation into operational and reporting workflows, improved efficiency, and made the most of the learning opportunities available in my role. At this stage, I am motivated to take the next step in my career by applying this experience in a broader environment with greater responsibility, continued learning, and stronger long-term impact."
      >
        Why am I looking for a new role?
      </button>
      <button
        type="button"
        class="faq-bubble"
        data-faq-question="Which locations am I open to working in?"
        data-faq-answer="I am based in North New Jersey and can comfortably commute to locations within approximately one hour by car across New Jersey. In addition, my area provides convenient access to New York, so I am fully open to roles in New York as well. Transportation and commute flexibility are not constraints for me."
      >
        Which locations am I open to working in?
      </button>
      <button
        type="button"
        class="faq-bubble"
        data-faq-question="What is my working style and execution approach?"
        data-faq-answer="My working style is adaptive, analytical, and improvement-focused. I actively align with evolving technologies and use them to make workflows more structured, trackable, and efficient. Depending on the need, I support operations through Python-based automation, SAP queries and reporting, and advanced Excel modeling and formula design. I enjoy tackling operational challenges, and I see process gaps as opportunities to learn, optimize, and deliver sustainable solutions. With a background in financial reporting, internal controls, audit discipline, and automation, I consistently focus on measurable results."
